- not raised: build_header (repro_bundle.rs:342) refuses names > 100 bytes (USTAR field limit) so a long-finding-id zip-slip via the `{finding_id}/{path}` join is bounded; finding ids are 16 hex chars per pass-10's notes on finding_id_hash. Confirmed safe at HEAD.
- not raised: verify_sha256 at repro_bundle.rs:417 hashes with BLAKE3 but the function is named `verify_sha256`; semantic mismatch only — the verifier and writer agree on the same hash family, so an attacker substituting an on-disk tar still gets caught. Cosmetic naming bug.
